replies.body:
{{champion:28}}  is fine in low elo as long as you learn how to position in team fights. Laning phase she's easy. be invis, pop up in a lane, get a kill. Teamfights she can be a little bit trickier but all in all, shes pretty good. And cheap.

Most the 450 and 1350 cheaps are "very easy" to play. Riot knows newer players like buying champs and so made the low cost ones easy to play.

4800 Junglers: {{champion:113}} {{champion:56}} {{champion:111}}  {{champion:106}} {{champion:62}} {{champion:57}} {{champion:64}} {{champion:59}} {{champion:105}} {{champion:72}} 

6300 Junglers: {{champion:203}} {{champion:121}} {{champion:120}} {{champion:266}} {{champion:60}} {{champion:245}} {{champion:131}} {{champion:107}} {{champion:421}} {{champion:223}} {{champion:154}} 

These are the "meta" junglers. You can also jungle {{champion:48}}  or {{champion:39}}  but lets focus on "real" junglers.

In terms of having damage and being easy to play, {{champion:62}} {{champion:59}}{{champion:245}}  {{champion:120}} {{champion:421}}  are your best bets.
